    <tr> 
      <td><br> <font face="Times New Roman" size="3"> 
              <p align="justify">  
        Under Transfer of Property Act, a mortgage of a specific immovable property 
        can be created for the purpose of securing the payment of money advanced 
        or to be advanced, or existing or future debt, the performance of an engagement 
        which may give rise to a pecuniary liability. Accordingly, equitable mortgage 
        can be for existing advances or for future advances and also for Non Fund 
        Based facilities, (which give raise to a pecuniary liability in future). 
        There are six types of mortgages recognised under the Transfer of Property 
        Act viz.</p>
        
      </font> <br>
    </td>
