    <tr> 
      <td>(<u><b>ii)Simple Mortgage: </b></u> <br>
        <br> <font face="Times New Roman" size="3"> 
              <p align="justify">  
        In a simple mortgage, without delivering possession of the mortgaged property, 
        the mortgagor binds himself by a mortgage deed to personally pay back 
        to the mortgagee and agrees that in the event of his failing to pay back 
        the money according to his contract, the mortgagee shall have a right 
        to cause the mortgaged property to be sold and the sale proceeds applied 
        in repayment of of the money. Simple mortgage is always in writing and 
        it attracts stamp duty as per the State Law. The stamped mortgage deed 
        duly executed by the mortgagor in favour of the Bank and attested by 2 
        witnesses is to be registered with the Registrar of Assurances. In the 
        revised set of documents, following documents have been introduced for 
        simple mortgage. They are: </p> </font></td>
