      <td><b><u>ii Equitable Mortgage:<br>
        <br>
        </u></b></td>
    </tr>
    <tr> 
      <td> <font face="Times New Roman" size="3"> 
              <p align="justify">  A detailed note on the definition, ingredients and the procedure on 
        how to create an equitable mortgage is available in Instruction Circular 
        No. 3072 which is reproduced herewith. The formats of Memorandum OF Deposit 
        of Title Deeds have been added to the List of Auxiliary Documents to enable 
        the Branches to have printed Memorandum copy readily at their end. However 
        in those case there are many properties and the details cannot be written 
        there in the format, the same may be typed out and typed copy may be used. 
        Similarly, the Declaration to be obtained from the Borrower-Mortgagor 
        stipulated by I.C. 3072 and those by Mortgagor-Guarantor provided by the 
        subsequent circular of Central Law Dept no. CLD: BBT dated 21-12-1995 
        and the Draft of Memorandum of Entry prescribed by Instruction Circular 
        3570 dated 02-11-1987 are included in the &#147;Other Documents&#148; 
        list of Chapter II. These declarations are to be obtained in non-judicial 
        stamp paper. </p> </font> 
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr> 
      <td><br> <font face="Times New Roman" size="3"> 
              <p align="justify">  
        The Instruction Circular no. 3072 among other things stipulated that a 
        Certificate from Income Tax authorities under Section 281(1)(ii) of Income 
        Tax Act has to be obtained and produced by the Mortgagor to the Bank while 
        creating equitable mortgage. Obtaining such certificate has been found 
        to be difficult and branches have requested for waiver of this stipulation 
        in I.C. 3072. The new Circular No. 6118 dated 15-11-2000 has granted certain 
        relaxation. The format for an affidavit in lieu of the I.T.C. has also 
        been incorporated in the &#147;other Documents&#148; in Part VIII of Chapter 
        II.</p> </font>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr> 
      <td><br> <font face="Times New Roman" size="3"> 
              <p align="justify">  
